Worn out fulcrum plates and paddle ends of the axle shafts can lead to a 
clunking that seems very much like a broken transmission mount. I think 
oversize fulcrum plates are available.


>So I've been getting a knocking/rattling sound when
>  I disengage the
>  clutch under a load (i.e. when starting up a hill).


